President Donald J. Trump received a briefing on the ongoing Federal response and recovery operations related to Hurricane Maria. He emphasized the importance of life-saving and life-sustaining efforts in the affected areas and stressed the need for continued support in Puerto Rico and the U.S. Virgin Islands. The President stated that there is no such thing as over-responding and expects long-term support from all elements of the Federal Government. He also praised the leadership of the Department of Homeland Security, Federal Emergency Management Agency, and the Governors of Puerto Rico and the U.S. Virgin Islands. The President expressed his thoughts and prayers for those affected and thanked the first responders for their dedication.